  <text>
    <body>
      <ab type="lido:objectWorkType">Leaflet</ab>
      <ab subtype="creation" type="lido:event">
        <date>1943 after</date>
      </ab>
      <ab type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">The frameless leaflet features a photograph of a couple. The man is holding the woman in his arms. He is looking at her but she not at him. She is wearing a dark costume, he a dark suit. Both have dark hair. The background is also dark; a wall lamp is switched on. In the lower part of the picture, the Serbo-Croatian title ‘Zabluda’ (Deception) is printed. The German original film title was ‘Die Gattin’ (The spouse).</ab>
      <ab subtype="comment" type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">Jenny Jugo and Willy Fritsch played the lead roles. The film was directed by Georg Jacoby and released in 1943.</ab>
